kdi capital partners  knowledge • discipline • integrity individuals we focus on growing and protecting the assets of individual investors each with varying risk tolerances while offering maximum transparency and daily liquidity advisors we partner with financial advisors and firms to provide investment solutions to generate the most suitable riskreturn results for their clients institutions we have a long track record of helping institutions achieve their investment goals through proven toptier public equity strategies financial roadmap kdi’s financial roadmap is a straightforward investment plan designed for high net worth clients to accumulate greater wealth through lower fees lower taxes and better investment results at kdi we have a longterm track record of investing in publicly traded equities for individuals corporations foundations and retirement plans we are based in raleigh north carolina our investment philosophy kdi is committed to reducing the risk associated with equity investing learn more our investment strategies kdi manages multiple equitybased strategies to suit its clients’ varying risk tolerances learn more in the news kdi capital partners was recently featured in the december  issue of business north carolina magazine read more kdi capital partners  about us about us our core principles kdi capital partners’ name comes from its three core operating principles knowledge discipline and integrity below we highlight some of the key tenets of each of these founding beliefs knowledge   invest in business models and companies where the investment team has considerable experience and coverage employ proprietary leveraged buyout lbo valuation model to assist in forecasting and comprehensive financial statement review confer with industry experts to enhance due diligence efforts in conducting primary research discipline   focus on great businesses which incorporate the following characteristics – growth predictability barriers to entry high returns on capital strong management teams and efficient capital allocation invest in a limited number of outstanding opportunities – generally  –  companies adhere to a strict buysell price discipline which is based on a private market valuation derived from our proprietary lbo model evaluate opportunities through the perspective of the private business owner with a long term view mitigate the risk of capital impairment with a willingness to hold significant amounts of cash and write call options against positions to create downside protection when riskreward dynamics are unfavorable integrity   align client and principal interests through significant coinvestment by principals seek to invest in management teams that exhibit a history of prioritizing strong corporate values commit to the highest standards and transparency in client relationships our philosophy kdi is committed to reducing the risk associated with equity investing to achieve this objective and to differentiate kdi as the manager of choice the firm has been guided by an investment philosophy and has utilized an investment process characterized by   commitment to value investing principles superior knowledge of focus market sectors and potential portfolio companies through extensive due diligence disciplined adherence to buy and sell parameters developed through comprehensive financial and qualitative analysis   one of the key philosophies of kdi is a belief that the principals should invest side by side with the clients our history the history of kdi dates to  when managing partner john day formed a partnership with investors management corporation imc the parent company of golden corral corporation to invest in publicly traded companies over time the partnership achieved impressive returns and attracted interest from outside investors   in  maynard capital partners llc mcp was formed to invest in public equities for investors outside of the imc organization the mcp name reflected the founding involvement of james maynard then chairman and ceo of imc and golden corral   as mcp continued to enjoy attractive investment results the firm grew in terms of its client base assets under management and market coverage in  sheldon fox joined the firm and became a partner in  also in  mcp changed its name to kdi capital partners llc to highlight the firm’s core operating principles knowledge discipline and integrity   today john day and sheldon fox are the majority owners of kdi with imc retaining a minority share meet our team kdi is a registered investment advisor based in raleigh north carolina the firm’s history dates back to  and is predominately employeeowned learn more about our team below the partners at kdi john m day cfa managing partner john has over  years of professional investment experience he joined investors management corporation imc in  since  he has had overall responsibility for imc’s partnership investments in publicly traded securities along with the formation and development of kdi john graduated from eastern illinois university in  and began his professional career in  as a cpa with kpmg llp in  he received an mba from the university of north carolina and then joined carolina securities corporation in raleigh where he worked for  years in  john earned the designation of chartered financial analyst sheldon m fox partner sheldon joined kdi capital partners in  after serving almost five years as chief financial officer of two bank holding companies ccb financial corporation and its’ successor by merger national commerce financial sheldon is a cpa and spent the first  years of his professional career with kpmg llp in raleigh he specialized in serving companies in the financial services industry and was admitted to the firm’s partnership as a tax partner in  sheldon earned an undergraduate degree from duke university in  the team at kdi shannon brown client services and trading coordinator shannon joined kdi capital partners in  and has performed several administra